data.chText: （基督教、犹太教和伊斯兰教的）先知
data.enText: (in the Christian, Jewish and Muslim religions) a person sent by God to teach the people and give them messages from God

data.chText: 穆罕默德（伊斯兰教的创始人）
data.enText: Muhammad, who founded the religion of Islam
a person who claims to know what will happen in the future
a person who teaches or supports a new idea, theory, etc.

data.chText: 威廉∙莫里斯是社会主义的早期传播者之一。
data.enText: William Morris was one of the early prophets of socialism.

data.chText: （《〈圣经〉旧约》和《希伯来圣经》中的）先知书
data.enText: the name used for some books of the Old Testament and the Hebrew Bible
a person who predicts that things will go very badly

data.chText: 认为电视会扼杀书籍的悲观预言家完全错了。
data.enText: The prophets of doom who said television would kill off the book were wrong.

tr: an authoritative person who divines the future
someone who speaks by divine inspiration
someone who is an interpreter of the will of God

value.def: A prophet is a person who is believed to be chosen by God to say the things that God wants to tell people.

example.ex: ...the sacred name of the Holy Prophet of Islam.

value.def: A prophet is someone who predicts that something will happen in the future.

example.ex: I promised myself I'd defy all the prophets of doom and battle back to fitness.
example.tran: 我发誓要打破所有的死亡预言，力争恢复健康。
